-- Fed Funds Projected to Open at 0.13% to 0.17%, ICAP Says
-- B y   L i z   C a p o   M c C o r m i c k
-- 2012-04-24T11:08:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-24/fed-funds-projected-to-open-at-0-13-to-0-17-icap-says.html
Fed funds, the U.S. overnight
inter-bank lending  rate , is projected to open at 0.13 percent to
0.17 percent, within the  Federal Reserve ’s target of zero to
0.25 percent.  Fed funds closed at 0.11 percent yesterday after trading
from 0.09 percent to 0.3125 percent and averaging 0.12 percent,
according to ICAP Plc, the world’s largest inter-dealer broker.
ICAP’s monthly average is 0.142 percent.  The central bank will acquire $4.25 billion to $5 billion
of Treasuries maturing from April 2018 to February 2020. The
purchases are part of the Fed’s program to replace $400 billion
of short-term debt in its portfolio with longer-term Treasuries
in an effort to reduce borrowing costs further and counter
rising risks of a recession.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Liz Capo McCormick in New York at 
